This is stored as an additional separate field on the document, as opposed to resolved, to enable sorting at the database layer
Mongo does not support sorting on properties of an array such as length
Note: Although this is a getter, the wrapper withEnumerableGettersTrait will allow the field to be enumerable when the instance is iterated
for example, when assigning / copying

entityId.description:
A copy of the entity id for the Knowledge Card, not exposed in the GraphQL schema
Internally used by resolvers or other processes to obtain a reference to the the comment's
Knowledge Card entity

parentCommentId.description:
parentCommentId is a reference to the comment that the comment is a reply to.
parentCommentId presence also implies that a comment is a reply.
The composite of the parentCommentId and the entityId allows retrieval of all reply comments for a
top-level comment and easily collating the total number of comments (incl. replies) on the asset.
This is because all comments (top-level and replies) are stored in a flat hierarchy in the database.
